All you gotta do is link to the stuff in my_rc_files.

Good times.

cd ~
git clone git@github.com:justfalter/my_rc_files.git
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.irbrc ~/.irbrc
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.screenrc ~/.screenrc
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.vim ~/.vim
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.tmux.conf ~/.tmux.conf
ln -s ~/my_rc_files/.tmux-osx.conf ~/.tmux-osx.conf


#######
Adding a submodule:

git submodule add https://github.com/majutsushi/tagbar.git .vim/bundle/tagbar
git commit


-----
Initializing my vim environment:

git submodule init
git submodule update

-----

Removing a submodule
- Delete the submodule from .gitmodules
- git rm --cached .vim/bundle/taglist.vim

